#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:3
#: 98f423c2d2a44b038c79c621c66833b5
msgid "Qrexec: socket-based services"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:6
#: 03935de3e09947d1943cd7223844d5c0
msgid ""
"*This page describes how to implement and use new socket-backed services "
"for qrexec. See* :doc:`qrexec </developer/services/qrexec>` *for general "
"overview of the qrexec framework.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:8
#: 8d345758f5c14574af7a1439391f93ec
msgid ""
"As of Qubes 4.1, qrexec allows implementing services not only as "
"executable files, but also as Unix sockets. This allows Qubes RPC "
"requests to be handled by a server running in a VM and listening for "
"connections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:11
#: 8d441eb35bd04dc286c909745dd3b050
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:14
#: 0b3b3abdc6ed4543b3b6c388453c48b7
msgid ""
"When a Qubes RPC service is invoked, qrexec searches for a file that "
"handles it in the qubes-rpc directories (``/etc/qubes-rpc`` or "
"``/usr/local/etc/qubes-rpc``). If the file is a Unix socket, qrexec will "
"try to connect to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:16
#: b4af633b9b85422b9c07e44266ce20f0
msgid ""
"Before passing user input, the socket service will receive a null-"
"terminated service descriptor, i.e. the part after ``QUBESRPC``. When "
"running in a VM, this is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:24
#: 45bf6c9d67374b1fb81564f11e189c1d
msgid "When running in dom0, it is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:32
#: efc33cb99b6843c8a421e52ee0f431f3
msgid ""
"(The target type can be ``name``, in which case target is a domain name, "
"or ``keyword``, in which the target is a keyword like ``@dispvm``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:34
#: f59c3bd7a9e44721888ebd0900d65177
msgid ""
"Afterwards, data provided by the service’s user (as stdin) is sent into "
"the socket, and data received from the socket is sent back to the user "
"(as stdout). When the service closes the socket, an exit code of 0 is "
"sent back to the user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:37
#: 263d9963df084b88a350a1aaa4f9b6fa
msgid "Differences from executable-based services"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:40
#: a1ddd45c581b456aae3ef2f153617a72
msgid ""
"From the user point of view, the socket-based service behaves almost like"
" an executable-based one. Here are the differences:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:42
#: bddcbd572e7b46a684d82f055170e6eb
msgid ""
"There is no stderr (the socket provides only one output stream). "
"Currently, that means stderr will also never be closed on user’s end."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:44
#: b1e932a3552b4e059edacf0edea0e057
msgid ""
"There is no exit code. When the socket connection is closed, exit code 0 "
"is sent to the user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:49
#: b05dae345fd345e69cbd48903fa52b81
msgid "Recommended use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:52
#: 985efd59beaf419c877edaf8bb16828f
msgid ""
"Create a program that binds to path *outside* ``/etc/qubes-rpc``, such as"
" ``/var/run/my-daemon.sock``. Put a symlink in ``/etc/qubes-rpc``, e.g. "
"``ln -s /var/run/my-daemon.sock /etc/qubes-rpc/qubes.Service``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-socket-services.rst:54
#: 436dff907342404eb5597865b7285060
msgid ""
"If your program handles multiple services, create multiple symlinks. You "
"can dispatch based on the service descriptor."
msgstr ""

